Concepts.definition: Having, relating to, or consisting of more than one individual, element, part, or other component; manifold.
An array of entities, such as light waves or particles, ordered in accordance with the magnitudes of a common physical property, such as wavelength or mass.
A visual representation of an object, scene, person or abstraction.
The tangible substance that goes into the makeup of a physical object.
The measured value of a response in a recorded image produced by the intensity, abundance, or concentration of source materials.
An independent acquisition scheme, i.e., a route or conduit through which flows data consisting of one particular measurement using one particular parameter.
An analysis (often in graphical form) representing the extent to which something exhibits various characteristics.
